            . I am a <rs id="t18220703-24-viclabel120" type="occupation">pencil-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-24-victim258 t18220703-24-viclabel120"></join>, and live in Salisbury-street, Strand. On the 16th of June, about a quarter before one o'clock in the afternoon, I was opposite <placeName id="t18220703-24-crimeloc121">St. Dunstan's-church</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-24-crimeloc121" type="placeName" value="St. Dunstan's-church"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-24-crimeloc121" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-24-off118 t18220703-24-crimeloc121"></join> - a gentleman tapped me on the shoulder, and said my pocket was picked; I found my silk handkerchief gone - upon turning round, I saw the prisoner with it in his hand; the gentleman had hold of him at the time; he said it dropped from my pocket, and he picked it up.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18220703-24-person260">
                  CHARLES 
                  THOMAS HODDER
               <interp inst="t18220703-24-person260" type="surname" value="THOMAS HODDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-24-person260" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-24-person260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the East India Company's service. About one o'clock on Sunday, I was in Fleet-street, and saw two gentlemen coming towards me arm in arm; the prosecutor was one of them - I observed a man close behind him; I watched him, and the moment they passed, I turned round, and saw the prisoner in the act of drawing a silk handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket - I immediately seized him; he had got it out and in his hand. I told the prosecutor. He said how could I say he had taken it, when he picked it up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-24-person261">
                  THOMAS 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18220703-24-person261" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
